FOODBORNE ILLNESS - AFGHANISTAN: (LAGHMAN) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 9 Aug 2018
Source: Pajhwok Afghan News [edited]
https://menafn.com/1097273906/350-people-fall-ill-after-eating-reception-food-in-Laghman


At least 350 people, including women and children, have been poisoned after eating food at a funeral reception in the Dawlat Shah district of eastern Laghman Province, an official said on Thursday [9 Aug 2018].

Sarhadi Zwak, the governor's spokesman, told Pajhwok Afghan News that the incident took place in Masmuti village of the district on Wednesday [8 Aug 2018]. He said 350 people were poisoned after consuming food at the funeral gathering and were immediately transported in ambulances to a nearby clinic. According to Zwak, the provincial public health department has dispatched an investigative team to the site, and a probe is currently under way into the incident.

Gulab Shah, a resident of the area, said the people who had fallen ill were in critical condition, as there were no transportation facilities to shift the poisoned people to healthcare centers.

